The field ravens can no longer be evicted from the cities, said experts on the first symposium about the crows in Leer, East Africa.
There experts from all over the Federal territory consulted on possible starting points.
Looking for alternatives in cities
In doing so, conservationists have also derived the problems of cities from the exodus of particularly protected field ravens: The use of chemistry in agriculture is probably increasingly destroying traditional areas for life.
Persecution, growing development and cutting down typical trees make it difficult for birds to nest.
Crows are protected.
