In addition, the overall recalculation of votes in all ballot boxes will be possible if there is an indication that the difference between the potential election winner and the candidate in second place is less than or equal to one percentage point; whenever there is an explicit request from the party's representative and/or the coalition that proposed the candidate in second place at the beginning of the session.
The overall recalculation of votes will also be possible if, after a proper addition, it is found that the difference between the likely winner and the candidate in second place is equal to or less than one percentage point, and whenever there is an explicit request from a political party whose candidate has finished second place, in which case the voting packages for which partial addition has been made will be eliminated.
