Fujimori was hospitalized again for medical tests
Former President Alberto Fujimori was hospitalized in a public hospital on Tuesday, where he will be tested for muscle loss, suffering from lower limbs, informed by his attending physician.
The 72 - year - old Fujimori, serving 25 years in prison for human rights violations committed by his government (1990 - 2000), suffers from several diseases, including tongue cancer, which has caused him to be operated four times and is under the control of doctors.
Member Alejandro Aguinaga, who is his personal physician, told Canal N television station that Fujimori will undergo tests within three days at the National Institute of Neoplastic Diseases, where they should find out why he is hurting and why he loses strength in his lower limbs.
Aguinaga said that in his opinion Fujimori could be pardoned for humanitarian reasons, however the former president himself does not wish mercy because he feels innocent.
He was operated on four times because of tongue cancer, lost 18 kg, and other problems were added as severe erosion gastritis, a cyst on the pancreas, kidney stones, high pressure and circulatory problems in the legs, the doctor named it.
Fujimori has been serving his sentence since September 2007 at the National Directorate of Special Police Operations.
In April 2009, he was sentenced to 25 years in prison for the death of 25 people killed by a murderous squadron of troops operating illegally in the early years of his reign.
