There was an eviction of the sheltered house where giant parties were held
Intruders have acquired 11 of the 13 apartments in the building in Balmes, 51
12 occupations left the house yesterday at noon without resisting
Everything suggests that the nightmare experienced by neighbors of number 51 on Balmes Street is finally over.
Twelve people volunteered to leave the building yesterday at noon, which they illegally inhabited, where they organized gigantic parties that woke the neighbors, leaving the building by court order, and without having to interfere with the police.
After the operation, the door lock was replaced to prevent a repeat of the situation.
"From now on, the entrance will be guarded," declared the administrator.
The occupiers who took 11 of the 13 apartments in the building - the rest of them inhabited - took away all electrical and partly water equipment, in addition to painting the walls and leaving behind garbage of all kinds, especially cans of alcoholic beverages.
The first three apartments hosted huge parties that lasted up to two days and woke up other tenants.
Next to the building is a discotheque, Balmes 51, which was also damaged.
The owner, Maria Pantinat, explained for Europa Press that sales fell by 80% while the building was occupied.
