Park or mountains?
The architects gathered on the occasion of the proceedings, which carry more than polemics regarding fees
The municipal tender for 16 gates once again opens up a debate on the role of the Collserola Park in Barcelona.
In the mid-1980s, at the time of the biggest boom of the already extinct Corporación Metropolitana de Barcelona (CMB), this government printed several pamphlets to support the Collserola park.
The flyer defined the mountain as a large park of metropolitan Barcelona.
What's more, it was supplemented by a numerical comparison with New York Central Park.
After CMB disappeared in 1987, the park returned to the minds of many as the upper limit of Barcelona. The Catalan metropolis is one of the few that are not oriented north - south, but up (mountain) - down (sea).
The qualification of Collserola as a natural park goes this way.
The reference was no longer Central Park, but Yellowstone with wild boars instead of Yogi bear.
This was the position until September, when the town hall announced a mega contest consisting of 16 auditions for the same number of entrance gates to Collserola.
Of course, the gate is recording more of a park idea.
It's either this, or someone's trying to place the gate in the field.
So there is only one question: Collserola, park or mountain?
During the competition, both in terms of purely organizational and on the basis of reflection on the city, this issue becomes the central theme of all Barcelona's architects.
It's already a subject as timid as when two members of this old caste chosen to meet in the elevator shake hands.
And it was this act that sparked one of the rare matches between what three Barcelonan architects and pre-conceived university professors think.
Miguel Roldan, Daniel Modol and Marta Bayona: the tender has its reasons.
According to Roldan, after the question of the bay side began, "it is necessary" to discuss the "mountain party" too, so Ildefons Cerd's speech on green apples was not brought to an end.
"We must build on the principle that Barcelona's largest park is the beach.
Among other things, its great availability.
Collserola is more complex," said the architect for whom the name "gates to Colliserola" carries a "lexicological trap": we must not imagine them "as entrances to the park, but rather as the definition of zones where it can operate".
Modol, like Roldan and Bayona with experience from the world of urbanism, qualifies the proposal as an "intellectual challenge" offering "some dangers."
The danger arising from the "uncertainty that is now represented by the public space project" after the experience of the 1980s, which had "its swan singing" in the Forum area.
The first concern is the very definition of the boundaries where it should be built.
"Something to define means to take the next step," that is, in principle, to move one step further.
"It is necessary to keep in mind the new urban and planning tools, because the current ones (with reference to the General Metropolitan Plan (PGM)) can cause a real disaster."
If we look more closely at the question, Modol believes that the Collserola valley slope can be "considered as a park" but not the Barcelona part, for reasons of purely topographical reasons.
Modol also recalled that there is already a work done by Patronat de Colliserola, who "may not end up in the junkyard" although he welcomes the fact that the town hall offers its grémia that it will intervene in the project from "the first moment."
Moreover, he understands that the proximity of the mountain and the city is a kind of culprit that allows architects to engage in the debate, but "doubtful" that it should be this technical profile that will be led by multidisciplinary teams ("it's all about skills," he adds), which need to be created: "Architects should only be instruments."
Bayona suggests that the answer to the question that gave the name of this game is complex because Collserola's global vision is missing in the tender documents: "16 competitions have been announced that deal with all the axes of the mountain - the sea, but there is no longitudinal study to look at the area and understand it as a whole."
This causes at least him to sign up for all 16 tenders.
Otherwise, the project of one gate may run into the concept and definition of the architect of the neighbouring gate.
In his view, the town hall should ensure that the zone located immediately above the Ronda de Dalt should ensure a full length of equipment to ensure a smooth transition between the city and greenery.
